Okay, so I need to explain how a transformer language model does next token prediction, focusing on attention, MLPs, and the residual stream. The user wants specifics about a 14B parameter model with a 5120 hidden size. Also, they want to know about output probabilities and training. Let me start by recalling what I know about transformers.

Transformers use self-attention mechanisms to process input sequences. Each token's representation is updated based on attention weights from all other tokens. Then there's the MLP (feed-forward network) part, which processes the attention output. The residual stream is the main path where all these operations happen, with residual connections adding the original input to the output of each layer.

